OL,3,CJersey's Council of Ministers meeting
OL,4,Cto discuss ferry dilemma
OL,6,FJersey's Council of Ministers met
OL,7,Ftoday to discuss how to proceed with
OL,8,Fthe decision about its new ferry
OL,9,Foperator. Following the meeting, a
OL,10,Fstatement was released.
OL,12,FIt read: "The Council of Ministers has
OL,13,Fhad positive discussions on our
OL,14,Flifeline ferry services.
OL,16,F"The questions asked of the operators
OL,17,Fwere in the best interests of Jersey's
OL,18,Fpublic and were on crucial elements of
OL,19,Foperator ownership, financial
OL,20,Fviability, and future investment in
OL,21,Fvessels.
