OL,3,CJersey's Council of Ministers meeting
OL,4,Cto discuss ferry dilemma
OL,6,FThe Minister then said: "I'm not angry
OL,7,Fwith Guernsey. I do understand that
OL,8,Fdifferent jurisdictions and different
OL,9,Fcountries have to look at their own
OL,10,Finterests.
OL,12,F"Guernsey has its perspective and
OL,13,Fthat's absolutely fine, but I am
OL,14,Fdetermined that Jersey tax payers know
OL,15,FI am acting for their benefit and on
OL,16,Ftheir behalf. That's the thing that
OL,17,Freally matters to me."
OL,19,FAfter this, he said he couldn't give a
OL,20,Ftimescale on when the decision would
OL,21,Fbe made.
